@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Hello";
}
@section featured {
    <section class="featured">
        <div class="content-wrapper">
            <hgroup class="title">
                <h1>@ViewBag.Title.</h1>
                <h2>@ViewBag.Message</h2>
            </hgroup>
            <p>
                If you are bridge enthusiast and you want to organize small tournaments on your own, 
                or you are participating in those kind of events and you want to have a tool for better organize and analyze them, you're in the rigth place. 
                If you are not, it is the best place to became one of us:)
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>
}
<h3>How to use this page:</h3>
<ol class="round">
    <li class="one">
        <h5>As bridge player</h5>
        You can simply log in, and either find your local bridge club or look for a new one in your neighbourhood. <br />
        You can subscribe to the tournaments in your clubs, check results, track history of your play. 
    </li>

    <li class="two">
        <h5>As tournaments organizer/director</h5>
        You can organize new tournament and let people to sign in on it. <br />
        But, the most importart what you can do here: you can easily <b>manage your tournament</b>. <br />
        Enter board results, generate standings, rosters, and everything else what is important for <b>tournament director</b>. 
    </li>

    
    <li class="three">
        <h3>What now?</h3>
        You should <a href="@Url.Action("Index","Tournament")"> log in or register</a>, and next go to the <a href="@Url.Action("Index","Tournament")">tournament list</a> and look for a new one or to create it.

</li>
</ol>
